snippet.textDisplay: You can colour your hair with food colouring! You just need to mix it with water and vinegar, then rise it through or dip it. It works pretty much immediately, but the longer its on the longer it lasts. Vinegar opens up your hair cuticle and the colour stains your hair, conditioner is too thick and doesn't deposit the colour.  I had really pretty cotton candy pink hair for a few months before I went back to my hairstylist and she was surprised how nicely it took.
snippet.textOriginal: You can colour your hair with food colouring! You just need to mix it with water and vinegar, then rise it through or dip it. It works pretty much immediately, but the longer its on the longer it lasts. Vinegar opens up your hair cuticle and the colour stains your hair, conditioner is too thick and doesn't deposit the colour.  I had really pretty cotton candy pink hair for a few months before I went back to my hairstylist and she was surprised how nicely it took.
